<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB04778</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT INSTITUTING REFORMS IN LAND ADMINISTRATION</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Intends to consolidate and streamline within a single government agency, land administration powers 
and functions (land surveys, mapping, classification, titling and disposition and registration) currently dispersed among the DOJ's Land Registration Authority and Registries of Deeds; and the DENR's Lands Management Bureau, Land Management Services in the regional, provincial and community offices, NAMRIA, and CARP Secretariat and its field offices.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ESCUDERO, EVELINA G.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-09-23</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON GOVERNMENT REORGANIZATION ON 2019-09-25</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SECONDARILY REFERRED TO THE COMMITTEE(S) ON NATURAL RESOURCES</td></tr></table>